{
  "texts": [
    "This is in line with the idea that the process model size influences the chunking strategy since the BPMN model size is greater than the natural text model size.",
    "The best results are obtained when applying the BPMN-specific chunking, showing remarkable accuracy (91.57 percent).",
    "This confirms the idea that a custom technique for chunking BPMN representations into semantically valid segments resulted in a significant enhancement in accuracy for the BPLLM pipeline, underscoring the efficacy of chunking strategies tailored to the specific process model representation.",
    "Moreover, favorable outcomes are obtained when fixed chunking and recursive chunking are used.",
    "In both cases, the optimal chunk size is 32 tokens with a 10-token overlap.Furthermore, Table 1 reports, in the third column, the refinement level (not refined and refined) of the adopted prompt."
  ]
}